> Dear Friends,
>
> Road conditions today were safe for cycling on the Wayne < > Chadds Ford
> Friday Frolic ride, using this route:
> http://ridewithgps.com/routes/1846480.  Some of the roads did have a
> layer of compressed leaves on the shoulders, but the roads were dry.
>
> There were no road closures or detours on our ride, but there were a few
> closures in the area, on other roads peripheral to our route:
>
>
> In Wayne, Croton Rd between Radnor Rd and Dewitt was closed, due to a
> fallen tree.
> In Malvern, Line Rd was closed north of Dutton Mill (heading toward Boot
> Rd & Paoli Pike)
> At the intersection of Darby Paoli Rd/PA-252 and White Horse Rd (this is a
> 3-way or "T"), the traffic lights were not functional.  A temporary stop
> sign was placed there.
>
> This is not hurricane-related, but.....White Horse Rd between Darby
> Paoli/252 and the curve at Wayland Rd is currently being MILLED.  A large,
> orange, "Rough Surface" sign has been posted.  The milling was not that
> severe for thin tires.
>
> In Chadds Ford, we passed a large downed wire in the shoulder of Brinton's
> Bridge Rd, a couple of miles after turning onto Brinton's Bridge from Creek
> Rd/PA-100.
>
> For the Halloween lovers: on West Wayne Ave, we passed large, single home
> across from Odorisio Park with a full-tilt, colorful, haunted Halloween
> display on the front lawn.  This is west of Conestoga Rd.
>
> Take care,
>
> Linda
